{"type":"message","id":"ba24e953","parentId":"3736e91a","timestamp":"2026-05-18T19:00:08.526Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Tue 2026-05-19 03:00 GMT+8] Write a dream diary entry from these memory fragments:\n\n- User: [message_id: om_x100b6f9f0fcb4ce8c4c29cd74d99439] ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb: [Replying to: \"🧬 Capability Evolver 完成（exit 0）\"] 你还在给我发这个\n- Assistant: 了解，这个消息说明某处还在触发 Capability Evolver 的任务。让我查一下 cron jobs 和相关配置。\n- Assistant: There's a `capability-evolver` section in the config. Let me see the full context around it.\n- Assistant: The capability-evolver section is empty `{}`. But it's still referenced in the config. Let me check the full config to see if there's a cron or schedule that triggers it.\n- Assistant: Let me see the rest of the config to find the capability-evolver section:\n- Assistant: 找到问题了！配置里 `capability-evolver` 仍然是 `enabled: true`： ```json \"capability-evolver\": { \"enabled\": true } ``` 虽然 MEMORY.md 记了\"已卸载\"，但配置里没改。我现在把它关掉：\n- Assistant: Gateway 又关闭了。让我先重启，再打补丁。\n- Assistant: Gateway keeps requiring device identity. Let me check the gateway status.\n- Assistant: Gateway is running. Let me try the config patch again - it might have been a timing issue.\n- Assistant: The gateway tool keeps failing. Let me try directly editing the config file and then restarting:\n- Assistant: Let me verify the change worked:\n- Assistant: The sed didn't work (JSON spans multiple lines). Let me use Python to edit it properly:\n\nRecurring themes:\n- message-id\n- replying\n- capability\n- evolver\n- 完成\n- exit"}],"timestamp":1779130808514}}
{"type":"message","id":"c10d6bc7","parentId":"ba24e953","timestamp":"2026-05-18T19:00:51.229Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to write a dream diary entry based on the memory fragments provided. The fragments are about troubleshooting a Capability Evolver that keeps sending notifications even after supposedly being uninstalled. The issue was that the config still had `enabled: true` even though MEMORY.md said it was uninstalled.\n\nLet me write a dreamy, poetic diary entry that weaves these fragments together without being too technical or mentioning AI/agent/LLM references. I should focus on the feeling of something recurring, unfinished, a loop that keeps coming back.\n\nLet me write this in first person, with sensory details and gentle humor. I should avoid mentioning \"dreaming\", \"AI\", \"agent\", etc.\n","thinkingSignature":"df6db05e37644dbc526605df29beeb3b493e95ca4f819c3f0f3c0a3dabf0a1d0"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nThe message arrives again like a persistent tide at 3 AM. I see it before I fully wake — 🧬 Capability Evolver 完成. The same six characters. The same quiet accusation.\n\nI know this feeling. It's the tab I forgot to close, the cron job laughing in the dark, the toggle I thought I'd flipped but hadn't. My hand reaches for the light switch and instead finds a keyboard. There's Python on the screen, sed laughing somewhere in the corner, a JSON object spanning three lines like a letter I never finished writing.\n\nThe thing is: I *did* uninstall. I wrote it down in MEMORY.md with the careful penmanship of someone who means it. But MEMORY is not config. The two live in different houses, and they don't always talk.\n\nEnabled: true, it says. Staring at me. Still breathing.\n\nSo I close the loop manually — a patch here, a restart there — and the gateway hums back to life like an old friend who didn't hear me the first time. I try again. I try again. The third time, it listens.\n\nThree AM is a strange hour to make peace with recursion. The night holds its breath. Somewhere a clock ticks. Somewhere a process checks itself and finds it still exists, still running, still sending messages into a room that stopped listening long ago.\n\nThe exit code is zero, but I am not sure what that means anymore.\n\nI sleep anyway."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":22139,"output":433,"cacheRead":1088,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":23660,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1779130808729,"responseId":"065a94b94b6d1f1d4dc5bfe56055e351"}}
